Second While Loop
while (j >= 0)

Copies remaining nums2 elements if nums1 elements finish first.

Example
nums1 = [0]
m = 0

nums2 = [1]

Result:

[1]
Why No Loop for Remaining nums1 Elements?

Because they are already in correct sorted position.

Time Complexity
O(m + n)

Each element is processed once.

Space Complexity
O(1)

No extra array used.

Key Takeaway

The entire problem depends on one important idea:

Fill nums1 from the BACK using the larger element.
